---
import SocialIcons from "./SocialIcons.astro";
---

<footer class="mt-auto py-6 border-t border-surface-700">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
    <!-- Dad joke generator -->
    <div class="mb-4 text-center">
      <button
        id="joke-btn"
        class="text-text-muted hover:text-flame-400 text-xs font-mono transition-all cursor-pointer group"
      >
        <span class="group-hover:hidden">🔥 click for a performance dad joke</span>
        <span class="hidden group-hover:inline">go on, you know you want to</span>
      </button>
      <p
        id="joke-text"
        class="text-flame-400 text-sm font-mono mt-2 hidden transition-all"
        style="text-shadow: 0 0 6px #fb923c40;"
      >
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
      <p class="text-text-muted text-xs">
        © {new Date().getFullYear()} Elena Tănăsoiu
        <span class="text-text-muted/30 ml-2 select-none" title="Try the Konami code...">↑↑↓↓←→←→BA</span>
        <span class="text-text-muted/50 ml-2 select-none text-xs" title="Press . for help">press <kbd class="text-flame-400/50">.</kbd> for secrets</span>
      </p>
      <SocialIcons />
    </div>
  </div>
</footer>

<script>
  const jokes = [
    "I told my manager we need to optimise. They said 'don't do it'. Technically correct.",
    "I cache everything. My therapist says I have commitment issues.",
    "Premature optimisation is the root of all evil. But late optimisation is the root of all pagers.",
    "How do you make a slow page faster? You don't. You make it do less.",
    "I profiled my morning routine. Turns out coffee is the bottleneck. Can't optimise that away.",
    "My code runs in O(1). One very long operation.",
    "My database query was so slow it applied for a mortgage while waiting.",
    "What did the load balancer say at the party? 'Don't worry, I'll spread the work around.'",
    "I asked my code why it was slow. It said 'I'm not slow, I'm thorough.'",
    "Caching is just hoarding with a fancy name and an expiry date.",
    "My pull request was so small it reduced latency by doing literally nothing. Best PR I ever wrote.",
    "I don't always write benchmarks, but when I do, I run them twice and pick the faster one.",
    "What do flamegraphs and onions have in common? Layers, and they both make you cry.",
    "My favourite optimisation pattern: 'Do it never.' Works every time.",
    "The server said it was fine. The flamegraph said it was lying.",
    "I named my cat 'Mutex' because she blocks everything.",
    "A cache miss walks into a bar. And then walks into the same bar. And then walks into the same bar.",
    "I explain my job as 'I stare at colourful rectangles until I find the one that shouldn't be there.' My mum thinks I'm an art critic.",
    "The five stages of performance debugging: denial, profiling, blame, 'oh it was DNS', acceptance.",
    "Ruby's garbage collector and I have the same approach to cleaning. We'll get to it eventually, and you really can't rush us.",
    "Why did the developer break up with their monitoring dashboard? Too many mixed signals.",
    "A flamegraph is just a stack trace having a midlife crisis - suddenly very concerned about how wide it's gotten.",
    "Profiling in production is like checking your bank balance after a night out. You know it's bad. You just need to know how bad.",
    "Why don't performance engineers ever get lost? They always know where the hotspots are.",
    "I love pickles and flamegraphs for the same reason: they both reveal what's been stewing for too long.",
    "What do you call a Ruby method that takes forever? A proc-rastinator.",
    "I moved from Romania to London for the weather. Just kidding. I moved for the lower latency.",
  ];

  const btn = document.getElementById("joke-btn");
  const text = document.getElementById("joke-text");
  let lastIndex = -1;

  btn?.addEventListener("click", () => {
    let index;
    do { index = Math.floor(Math.random() * jokes.length); } while (index === lastIndex);
    lastIndex = index;
    if (text) {
      text.textContent = jokes[index];
      text.classList.remove("hidden");
    }
  });
</script>
